WhatNew Wholesale Category Policy

WhatNew Support March 27, 2025 at 4:26 PM

{/* ===== Seller Wholesale Category Section ===== */}

WhatNew Wholesale Category Policy

WhatNew’s Wholesale Category is designed to support high-volume transactions and reseller product sourcing, including the sale of pallets, casepacks, and bundled inventory. These policies promote transparency, consistency, and trust between sellers and buyers.

Currently, the Wholesale Category is available in the U.S., France, and Germany. France and Germany are in beta testing.

On this page:

  • What is sold in the Wholesale category (US)
  • Buyers in Wholesale Category (US)
  • Seller Requirements – Wholesale Category (US)

Wholesale Subcategories

There are two subcategories under Wholesale:

  • Pallets
  • Casepacks & Bundles

Selling in the Pallets Subcategory

A pallet is a bulk collection of items (typically 100+). Inventory may be wholesale or liquidation. Pallets ship via Freight through our partner Blue Grace.

Selling in Casepacks & Bundles

Casepacks and bundles include lots of 10+ units for resale, shipped via standard WhatNew labels. Casepacks are uniform units; bundles are mixed inventory.

Buyers in the Wholesale Category (US)

Buyers should review manifests, listings, and seller details carefully to understand product type, condition, and source.

Buyer Shipping Considerations

  • Pallets: Sellers ship within 3 business days. Freight carriers contact buyers within 3 days. Average delivery is 1–3 weeks.
  • Casepacks & Bundles: Must be shipped within 2 business days per WhatNew policy.

Seller Requirements – Wholesale Category (US)

Sellers must comply with WhatNew policies and maintain transparency through manifests and disclosures.

Pallet Disclosure Requirements

  • Type and quantity of items
  • Condition of items
  • [Optional] Brands included, MSRP, and unique SKU count

Casepack & Bundle Disclosure

Detailed manifests are optional, but sellers must follow the Single Surprise Product Policy — descriptions must be accurate and transparent.

Condition Details

  • Accurately describe the condition of all items.
  • Disclose defects, missing parts, or wear and tear.

No Individual Pallet Items

Sellers cannot sell individual items from pallets in this category. For mixed sales, use Casepacks & Bundles or another WhatNew category.

Prohibited or Restricted Items

  • Expired items (less than 3 months from expiration)
  • Cosmetics older than 3 years
  • “Not for resale” items

Shipping in Wholesale

Pallets

  • Ship within 3 business days via Blue Grace Logistics.
  • Update tracking through BYOL (Bring Your Own Label).
  • Only available within the contiguous U.S.

Casepacks & Bundles

  • Ship within 2 business days per WhatNew’s policy.

Refunds

Sellers must comply with WhatNew’s Buyer Protection Policy for refund processing.

Tax Exemption

  • Apply for tax exemption before purchasing by submitting valid documents.
  • No retroactive refunds for unapproved purchases.

Helpful Walkthroughs & Resources

  • Scheduling a pallet show and creating a listing
  • Running your pallet show
  • Fulfillment and uploading tracking information
